        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>This spell isnt a replacement or upgrade to Ignite/Chill bones.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P><b>Ignite Bones</b> -</P><P>Mana: 210<BR>Cast Time: 6.1 seconds<BR>Effect: 500 DD (Fire based), angry melee, failed raids.<BR>Buyable.<BR>Ratio of 2.38 damage/mana.</P><P>Chill Bones -</P><P>Mana: 210<BR>Cast Time: 6.1 seconds<BR>Effect: 500 DD (Cold based), angry melee, failed raids.<BR>Dropped.<BR>Ratio of 2.38 damage/mana.</P><P><b>Insiduous Retrogression</b> - </P><P>Mana: 210<BR>Cast Time: 6.1 seconds<BR>Recast Time: 12 seconds<BR>Effect: 551 DD (Disease based), snare effect (60%), debuff.<BR>Buyable.<BR>Ratio of 2.62 damage/mana.</P><P>I remember reading a long thread about how terrible our ignite and chill bones spells were, etc, etc. Among the requests were that the skeleton illusion be removed, the resists be lowered, etc. This spell has <b>no</b> illusion, resists <b>disease</b> does <b>more</b> damage, is <b>buyable</b> and in addition, snares.</P><P>And people are complaning about how long the snare lasts.</P><P>- Drash Theardark - Aquagnome</font></td>
