        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Snare taunt is dependent on the mobs. Some mobs wont give a crap if you snare them, and some will agro you till you're a splatted corpse. Having played a Ranger for 55 levels, you get an idea of what to snare, and more importantly, when. Juggs for example absolutely, and totally HATE snare. It doesn't matter if you snare at the end or not, they will most likely summon you, whereas if you're doing Chardok and land your IR on anything but the doggies, they don't really care. The dogs however will try and tear you apart.</P><P>IR with my Necro is a fantastic spell. I have it mem'd nearly all the time and it doesn't cause me much agro at all on most mobs I face. I'm glad it isn't a DoT, though.. That would blow. As for it being dis-spelled in PvP.. I thought diseased based spells were immune to that?</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
